# Project-1
EVA project 1-- Basics of CNN, Kernels and max pooling


1) What are Channels and Kernels (according to EVA)?
Kernel/feature extractor/filter is a matrix which when applied on an image, it separates all instances of a particular channel (think edges or arcs).
1 pea

Technically,weight matrix in CNN will be a matrix of kernel.

Channels are Ingredients of an Image.Channels are similar set of image features which can be obtained by applying a convolution kernel. 


Why should we only (well mostly) use 3x3 Kernels?

We would like the kernels to satisfy following 2 properties-
1) Smaller dimension- This would tantamount to less number of parameters needed to train a CNN. 
2) Odd and sqare matrix - Odd provides a good symmetry.

How many times do we need to perform 3x3 convolution operation to reach 1x1 from 199x199 (show calculations)
99 times

